5:
Who are you? How much is he paying 
you?
9:
No one is paying us. We saw that the 
child needed help!
12:
Hah! "Needed help..." That's a good 
one.
16:
When the kid wakes up, tell him this. 
The "Hellcat of the Dunes" is still alive.
18:
And long as I've got my fangs and 
claws, his two-faced "lord" better stay 
awake at night.
26: Alk! Leave him. The child comes first.
48: Why... Why are there more of them?!
58:
You are hurt. You need a safe place 
to rest.
63:
And, to tell the truth, so do we. We're 
lost, and you're kind of our only hope 
right now.
65: So you don't have to be scared, okay?
67:
We are here to help you. What is your 
name?
74: Nadir. Can you lead us home?
77:
I don't have a home. All of the soldiers 
live with the Lord of the Oasis.
82:
We will take you back to your lord. 
Perhaps then you'll see I mean you no 
harm.
90:
Not just "someone." His savior. The 
whole oasis was talking about it.
97:
Lord Rolan. The hellcat was kept 
as a freak show, until Lord Rolan 
bought his freedom.
99:
The lord was famous for being... 
unique. Even people from the 
borderlands know him. ...Where are 
you from, anyways?
108:
We come from beyond the 
borderlands. We've traveled a long 
way, and have need of information.
110:
Tell me... Why were you hunting the 
tiger alone? He may be a murderer, 
but you are only a child.
115:
What's special about being a kid? 
There's plenty of us around.
119:
Why would that tiger kill the man 
who saved him?
131:
Hey. I don't know why, but something 
about what we just heard... just 
doesn't sit right with me.
134: Yes. I think there's more to the story...
